#credit: http://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/model_selection/plot_learning_curve.html
def plot_learning_curve(estimator, title, X, y, ylim=None, cv=None,
                        n_jobs=1, train_sizes=np.linspace(.1, 1.0, 5)):

    plt.figure()
    plt.title(title)
    if ylim is not None:
        plt.ylim(*ylim)
    plt.xlabel("Training examples")
    plt.ylabel("Score")
    train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(
        estimator, X, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=n_jobs, train_sizes=train_sizes, scoring ='f1')
    train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
    train_scores_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)
    plt.grid()

    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_scores_mean - train_scores_std,
                     train_scores_mean + train_scores_std, alpha=0.1,
                     color="r")
    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_scores_mean - test_scores_std,
                     test_scores_mean + test_scores_std, alpha=0.1, color="g")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, 'o-', color="r",
             label="Training score")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores_mean, 'o-', color="g",
             label="Cross-validation score")

    plt.legend(loc="best")
    return plt

def get_optimal_rf_features(x_train, y_train, rf_features_to_keep, rf_model):
    
    importances = rf_model.feature_importances_
    all_indices = np.argsort(importances)
    results = []

    for i in rf_features_to_keep:
        indices = all_indices[-1*i:-1]
        feature_selected_x_train = x_train.iloc[:,list(indices)]
        cv_score = cross_val_score(rf_model, feature_selected_x_train, y=y_train, scoring='f1', cv=cv, n_jobs=1, verbose=0)
        results.append([i, cv_score.mean()])
    
    return pd.DataFrame(results, columns = ['Number of Top Features', 'CV F1 Score for RF'])

##credit for this function and the one below goes to fellow classmate jtay (github user name) etc
##code was used for Georgia Tech's ML class and we have permission to use for personal usage.
def reconstructionError(projections,X):
    W = projections.components_
    if sps.issparse(W):
        W = W.todense()
    p = pinv(W)
    reconstructed = ((p@W)@(X.T)).T 
    errors = np.square(X-reconstructed)
    return np.nanmean(errors)

    #print(str(n)+ ' Reconstruction Error: %.4f' % rce)
    pca_variances.append((n,explained_variance,pca_explained, rce))
    j+=1

pca_data = pd.DataFrame(pca_variances, columns=['Number of Components','Cumulative Explained Variance', 'Component Explained Variance','Reconstruction Error'])

### PERFORMANCE OF K MEANS AND EM CLUSTERING WITH NUMBER OF CLUSTERS
clusters =  [2,3,5,8,10,12,15,20,25,30,35,40,50,60,75,100]

SSE = defaultdict(dict)
ll = defaultdict(dict)
bic = defaultdict(dict)
aic = defaultdict(dict)
silhoutte = defaultdict(dict)

km = kmeans(random_state=RANDOM_SEED, init ='k-means++')
gmm = GMM(random_state=RANDOM_SEED)

st = clock()
for k in clusters:
    #print(k)
    km.set_params(n_clusters=k)
    gmm.set_params(n_components=k)
    #print('fitting')
    km.fit(feature_selected_x_train)
    gmm.fit(feature_selected_x_train)
    
    #print(km.score(feature_selected_x_train))
    #print(gmm.score(feature_selected_x_train))
    #print(gmm.bic(feature_selected_x_train))  
    #print(gmm.aic(feature_selected_x_train))
    
    SSE[k]['Clustering'] = km.score(feature_selected_x_train)
    ll[k]['Clustering'] = gmm.score(feature_selected_x_train)
    bic[k]['Clustering'] = gmm.bic(feature_selected_x_train)  
    aic[k]['Clustering'] = gmm.aic(feature_selected_x_train)   

SSE = (-pd.DataFrame(SSE)).T
ax = SSE.plot(legend =False, title = 'K-Means SSE vs Number of Clusters')
ax.set_xlabel("Number of Clusters")
ax.set_ylabel("SSE")
plt.show()

ax.set_xlabel("Number of Clusters")
ax.set_ylabel("Log Likelihood")

test_results = []
def get_results(model_name, true_labels, pred_label):
    acc = sklearn.metrics.accuracy_score(true_labels, pred_label)
    p = sklearn.metrics.precision_score(true_labels, pred_label)
    r = sklearn.metrics.recall_score(true_labels, pred_label)
    f1 = sklearn.metrics.f1_score(true_labels, pred_label)
    return [model_name, f1,p,r,acc]

In [154]:
logreg_model.fit(projected_x_train, y_train)
log = logreg_model.predict_proba(projected_x_test)

rf_model.fit(feature_selected_x_train, y_train)
rf = rf_model.predict_proba(feature_selected_x_test)

gbm_model.fit(feature_selected_x_train, y_train)
gbm = gbm_model.predict_proba(feature_selected_x_test)

nn_model.fit(projected_x_train, y_train)
nn = nn_model.predict_proba(projected_x_test)


ensemble_preds = 0.25*log + 0.25*rf + 0.25*gbm + 0.25*nn
ensemble_preds = ensemble_preds[:,1]
ensemble_preds[ensemble_preds>=0.5]  = 1
ensemble_preds[ensemble_preds<0.5]  = 0

print('Model Predictions Correlations with Each Other')
print(np.corrcoef(log[:,1], rf[:,1])[0,1])
print(np.corrcoef(log[:,1], gbm[:,1])[0,1])
print(np.corrcoef(log[:,1], nn[:,1])[0,1])
print(np.corrcoef(nn[:,1], rf[:,1])[0,1])
print(np.corrcoef(nn[:,1], gbm[:,1])[0,1])
print(np.corrcoef(gbm[:,1], rf[:,1])[0,1])

test_results.append(get_results('Weighted Ensemble (Best 4 Models)', y_test, ensemble_preds))
test_results_df = pd.DataFrame(test_results, columns = ['Model','F1', 'Precision','Recall', 'Accuracy'])
test_results_df = test_results_df.sort_values('F1',ascending='False')
test_results_df.round(3)
